This little guy was sent to the shop by his mom.
His name is Peter.
He is about to reach age 10.
He is scared. 
His mom, Laura runs up to him.
Mom says, dont be, its natural. 
Mom says, be strong, you are my son, you have to be.
Kiddo hold back his tears, stands up, says, "I WILL DO IT MAM"
He is still scared as hell, but he can't show it.
He can see in her face, shes deeply proud.
Peter starts goin into the shop, a lot of "big" people are there.
Mom said to peter, ask the cashier if he doenst find anything.
Peter ask the pretty lady, "Miss, where can i find the milk?"
The Miss says, at the back of the shop.
He goes there, confused, there are a lof of milk.
Can not decide, he sits there for about 2hours, trying to decide.
He stars crying, sayin, "Mommy, its too hard".
Cashier sees it, runs up to him, she helps him.
Decided to buy the one nammed "Mizo Boci"
Peter is happy.
Peter is happier than ever.
Thinking his mom is gonna be proud.
Almost home.
Peter is actually running home, hes that happy.
Goes into the house.
Searching for mom.
Can't find her.
Mommy left.
Relatives are there, they say "We are gonna take care of you Peter, dont worry!". 

End of story.
